cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY

The paper discusses the use of VOSviewer for analyzing large amounts of text data, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on bibliometric maps of science. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as text mining is a common technique in this field. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper discusses the analysis of text data. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as VOSviewer can be used to analyze networks of authors and citations. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the use of VOSviewer for analyzing scientific literature.
